SIMPLE: no-mans-land
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: No-mans-land
<hw>No"-man's`-land`</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A space amidships used
to keep blocks, ropes, etc.; a space on a ship belonging to no one in
particular to care for.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An unoccupied area between opposing
armies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark>: <def>An
unclaimed space or time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>no-man's land</qex> of twilight.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Black.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nomarch</ent>⟦br⟧
